<Narrative>
	<Paragraph>
		The morning light came in low across the harbor, turning the water the color
		of old brass.
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		She had been walking for an hour before she realized she had left without
		her keys.
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		It did not matter. She was not going back.
	</Paragraph>
</Narrative>
